<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="889">Note:</emphasis>
Smith &amp; Downs (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="889">Fl. Neotropica</emphasis>
14: 972. 1977) indicated unspecified material in 
<specimenReference collectionCode="BM-SL">
Herb. Sloane (
<collectionCode>BM-SL</collectionCode>
)
</specimenReference>
as type. However, although Linnaeus referred to a Sloane polynomial in the protologue, it was (unusually) unaccompanied by an illustration. The material would not have been seen by Linnaeus and cannot be original material for the name, nor is there any other. Till therefore designated a 
<typeStatus>
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
</typeStatus>
from Jamaica.
</paragraph>
